Added the following new NP error traps: brcdNPMemoryParityErrorTrap brcdNPMemoryMiscErrorTrap brcdNPBuffOverFlowErrorTrap brcdNPBuffUnderFlowErrorTrap brcdNPECCSingleErrorTrap brcdNPECCMultipleErrorTrap

Added table brcdNPBufferErrorTable, notification snTrapNPIngressBufferErrorThresholdExceeded, and notification snTrapNPEgressBufferErrorThresholdExceeded for CER/CES Data Integrity Protection.
Changes in this revision: - Updated below mib table descriptions with LAG interface support: brcdNPQosStatTable brcdTMDestUcastQStatTable
Changes in this revision: - Added below new tables brcdNPQosStatTable brcdTMDestUcastQStatTable

brcdNPStatsTable.name: brcdNPStatsTable
brcdNPStatsTable.description: A list of brcdNPStats entries. This table contains information of various Network Processor(NP) counters supported by this system.

brcdNPStatsEntry.name: brcdNPStatsEntry
brcdNPStatsEntry.description: An entry containing NP counter information applicable for a particular interface if the module is physically present.

brcdNPStatsIfIndex.name: brcdNPStatsIfIndex
brcdNPStatsIfIndex.description: Interface index as equivalent to ifIndex in MIB II. This is applicable only for the interfaces that are physically present and operationally up.

brcdNPStatsRxRawGoodPkts.name: brcdNPStatsRxRawGoodPkts
brcdNPStatsRxRawGoodPkts.description: Counter for good packets received from MAC. In equation, Rx Raw Good Packets = Rx Unicast Packets + Rx Multicast Packets + Rx Broadcast Packets = Rx IPv4 Packets + Rx IPv6 Packets + Rx Other Packets = Rx Forward Packets + Rx Discard Packets

brcdNPStatsRxForwardPkts.name: brcdNPStatsRxForwardPkts
brcdNPStatsRxForwardPkts.description: Counter for forwarded packets by packet evaluation engine in the Ingress. In equation, Rx Forward Packets = Rx Sent to TM Packets + Rx RL drop packets .

brcdNPStatsRxDiscardPkts.name: brcdNPStatsRxDiscardPkts
brcdNPStatsRxDiscardPkts.description: Counter for packets flagged for discard by packet evaluation engine. In equation, Rx Discard Packets = ACL drop + TTL drop + route-only drop + RPF drop + tag mismatch drop + VLAN blocking drop + segment filtering drop + drop by packet evaluation decisions + miscellaneous.

brcdNPStatsRxSendToTMPkts.name: brcdNPStatsRxSendToTMPkts
brcdNPStatsRxSendToTMPkts.description: Counter for packets sent to TM. This value should be equal to difference of Rx forward packets and RL drops.

brcdNPStatsRxBadPkts.name: brcdNPStatsRxBadPkts
brcdNPStatsRxBadPkts.description: Counter for bad packets in the receiver side. They represent the packets that have MAC to NP interface errors.

brcdNPStatsRxLookupUnavailable.name: brcdNPStatsRxLookupUnavailable
brcdNPStatsRxLookupUnavailable.description: Number of packets that have been dropped due to unavailability of the CAM interface for packet lookups.

brcdNPStatsRxACLDrop.name: brcdNPStatsRxACLDrop
brcdNPStatsRxACLDrop.description: Drop counter for ACL drop on the ingress path.

brcdNPStatsRxPriority0And1Drop.name: brcdNPStatsRxPriority0And1Drop
brcdNPStatsRxPriority0And1Drop.description: Counter for packets dropped based on Priority 0,1 in the Ingress.

brcdNPStatsRxPriority2And3Drop.name: brcdNPStatsRxPriority2And3Drop
brcdNPStatsRxPriority2And3Drop.description: Counter for packets dropped based on Priority 2,3 in the Ingress.

brcdNPStatsRxPriority4And5Drop.name: brcdNPStatsRxPriority4And5Drop
brcdNPStatsRxPriority4And5Drop.description: Counter for packets dropped based on Priority 4,5 in the Ingress.

brcdNPStatsRxPriority6And7Drop.name: brcdNPStatsRxPriority6And7Drop
brcdNPStatsRxPriority6And7Drop.description: Counter for packets dropped based on Priority 6,7 in the Ingress.

brcdNPStatsRxSuppressRPFDrop.name: brcdNPStatsRxSuppressRPFDrop
brcdNPStatsRxSuppressRPFDrop.description: Counter for suppressed RPF drops on the ingress path due to ACL override.

brcdNPStatsRxRPFDrop.name: brcdNPStatsRxRPFDrop
brcdNPStatsRxRPFDrop.description: Counter for RPF drop in the ingress.

brcdNPStatsRxIPv4Pkts.name: brcdNPStatsRxIPv4Pkts
brcdNPStatsRxIPv4Pkts.description: Raw packet count that have IPv4 Etype (0x0800) and IP version of 0x4.

brcdNPStatsRxIPv6Pkts.name: brcdNPStatsRxIPv6Pkts
brcdNPStatsRxIPv6Pkts.description: Raw packet count that have IPv6 Etype (0x86DD) and IP version of 0x6.

brcdNPStatsRxRouteOnlyDrop.name: brcdNPStatsRxRouteOnlyDrop
brcdNPStatsRxRouteOnlyDrop.description: Counts packets that have been dropped due to Route-Only configuration during MAC-DA processing.

brcdNPStatsRxIPv6SuppressRPFDrop.name: brcdNPStatsRxIPv6SuppressRPFDrop
brcdNPStatsRxIPv6SuppressRPFDrop.description: Counter for IPv6 suppressed RFP drops on the ingress path due to ACL override.

brcdNPStatsRxIPv6RPFDropCount.name: brcdNPStatsRxIPv6RPFDropCount
brcdNPStatsRxIPv6RPFDropCount.description: Counter for IPv6 drop on the ingress.

brcdNPStatsRxIPv4Bytes.name: brcdNPStatsRxIPv4Bytes
brcdNPStatsRxIPv4Bytes.description: Raw packet Bytes (+FCS) that have IPv4 Etype (0x0800) and IP version equals 0x4.

brcdNPStatsRxIPv6Bytes.name: brcdNPStatsRxIPv6Bytes
brcdNPStatsRxIPv6Bytes.description: Raw packet Bytes (+FCS) that have IPv6 Etype (0x86DD) and IP version equals 0x6.

brcdNPStatsRxPOSCtrlProtocolPkts.name: brcdNPStatsRxPOSCtrlProtocolPkts
brcdNPStatsRxPOSCtrlProtocolPkts.description: Number of control protocol packets received in POS mode. The object is supported only on POS interfaces. 0 is returned for others.

brcdNPStatsRxPOSLinkDrop.name: brcdNPStatsRxPOSLinkDrop
brcdNPStatsRxPOSLinkDrop.description: Number of packets dropped due to link state in POS mode. The object is supported only on POS interfaces. 0 is returned for others.

brcdNPStatsRxRoutedPktsDrop.name: brcdNPStatsRxRoutedPktsDrop
brcdNPStatsRxRoutedPktsDrop.description: Number of received IPv4 or IPv6 routed packets that are dropped because the TTL is 0, or because routing is not enabled on the given virtual interface.

brcdNPStatsTxSentToMACPkts.name: brcdNPStatsTxSentToMACPkts
brcdNPStatsTxSentToMACPkts.description: Total number of packets sent to MAC for transmit.In equation, Tx Sent to MAC = Tx IPv4 Packets + Tx IPv6 Packets + Tx Others = Tx Raw Good Packets - Tx Source Port Suppression Drop - Tx ACL drop - Tx RL Drop - Tx Multicast TTL drop.

brcdNPStatsTxRawGoodPkts.name: brcdNPStatsTxRawGoodPkts
brcdNPStatsTxRawGoodPkts.description: Total number of packets sent to egress processing logic that pass the initial length checks (min, max, offsets, bad packet etc.)In equation, Tx Raw Good Packets = Tx Receive From TM Packets - Tx Bad Packets = Tx Unicast Packets + Tx Broadcast Packets + Tx Multicast Packets + Tx Source Port Suppression Drop.

brcdNPStatsTxSrcPortSupressDrop.name: brcdNPStatsTxSrcPortSupressDrop
brcdNPStatsTxSrcPortSupressDrop.description: Number of packets dropped because of transmit source port suppression.

brcdNPStatsTxBadPktsCnt.name: brcdNPStatsTxBadPktsCnt
brcdNPStatsTxBadPktsCnt.description: Total number of packets dropped in egress logic that fail the initial length checks (min, max, bad packet etc.).

brcdNPStatsTxReceiveFromTM.name: brcdNPStatsTxReceiveFromTM
brcdNPStatsTxReceiveFromTM.description: Counter for packets received from TM.

brcdNPStatsTxACLDrop.name: brcdNPStatsTxACLDrop
brcdNPStatsTxACLDrop.description: Number of packets that have been dropped by the outbound ACL logic.

brcdNPStatsTxPFCMulticastDrop.name: brcdNPStatsTxPFCMulticastDrop
brcdNPStatsTxPFCMulticastDrop.description: Number of multicast FID packets that have been dropped by egress logic that map to the egress queue which is in paused state. Supported only on 'NI-MLX-10Gx8-D 8-port 10GbE Module', 'NI-MLX-10Gx8-M 8-port 10GbE (M) Module', 'NI-MLX-10Gx8-X 8-port 10GbE (X) Module', 'BR-MLX-40Gx4-M 4-port 40GbE Module', 'BR-MLX-10Gx20 20-port 1/10GbE Module', 'BR-MLX-100Gx2-CFP2 2-port 100GbE Module' and 'BR-MLX-10Gx4-M-IPSEC 4-port 10GbE Module'. 0 is returned for the rest of the cards.

brcdNPStatsTxPFCMTUExceedDrop.name: brcdNPStatsTxPFCMTUExceedDrop
brcdNPStatsTxPFCMTUExceedDrop.description: Number of packets that have been dropped by egress logic that exceeds the MTU of the egress queue (they map to). Supported only on 'NI-MLX-10Gx8-D 8-port 10GbE Module', 'NI-MLX-10Gx8-M 8-port 10GbE (M) Module', 'NI-MLX-10Gx8-X 8-port 10GbE (X) Module', 'BR-MLX-40Gx4-M 4-port 40GbE Module', 'BR-MLX-10Gx20 20-port 1/10GbE Module', 'BR-MLX-100Gx2-CFP2 2-port 100GbE Module' and 'BR-MLX-10Gx4-M-IPSEC 4-port 10GbE Module'. 0 is returned for the rest of the cards.

brcdNPStatsTxPFCQMAPErrorDrop.name: brcdNPStatsTxPFCQMAPErrorDrop
brcdNPStatsTxPFCQMAPErrorDrop.description: Number of packets that have been dropped by egress logic that does not map to any valid egress queue. This object is Supported only on 'NI-MLX-10Gx8-D 8-port 10GbE Module', 'NI-MLX-10Gx8-M 8-port 10GbE (M) Module', 'NI-MLX-10Gx8-X 8-port 10GbE (X) Module', 'BR-MLX-40Gx4-M 4-port 40GbE Module', 'BR-MLX-10Gx20 20-port 1/10GbE Module', 'BR-MLX-100Gx2-CFP2 2-port 100GbE Module' and 'BR-MLX-10Gx4-M-IPSEC 4-port 10GbE Module'. 0 is returned for the rest of the cards.

brcdNPStatsTxIPv4Pkts.name: brcdNPStatsTxIPv4Pkts
brcdNPStatsTxIPv4Pkts.description: Number of IPv4 packets transmitted out the port that have Etype 0x0800 and IPver version equals 0x4)

brcdNPStatsTxIPv6Pkts.name: brcdNPStatsTxIPv6Pkts
brcdNPStatsTxIPv6Pkts.description: Number of IPv6 packets transmitted out the port that have Etype 0x86DD and IPver version equals 0x6.

brcdNPStatsTxIPv4Bytes.name: brcdNPStatsTxIPv4Bytes
brcdNPStatsTxIPv4Bytes.description: Counts packet Bytes (+FCS) that have IPv4 Etype (0x0800) and IP version equals 0x4

brcdNPStatsTxIPv6Bytes.name: brcdNPStatsTxIPv6Bytes
brcdNPStatsTxIPv6Bytes.description: Counts packet Bytes (+FCS) that have IPv6 Etype (0x86DD) and IP version equals 0x6

brcdNPStatsTxPOSCtrlProtocolPkts.name: brcdNPStatsTxPOSCtrlProtocolPkts
brcdNPStatsTxPOSCtrlProtocolPkts.description: Number of control protocol packets sent in POS mode. The object is supported only for POS interfaces. For others it returns 0.

brcdNPStatsTxPOSLinkDrop.name: brcdNPStatsTxPOSLinkDrop
brcdNPStatsTxPOSLinkDrop.description: Number of packets dropped due to link state in POS mode. The object is supported only for POS interfaces. For others it returns 0.

brcdNPBufferErrorTable.name: brcdNPBufferErrorTable
brcdNPBufferErrorTable.description: A list of brcdNPBufferError entries. This table contains information of various Network Processor(NP) error event counters supported by this system. The objects in this table are refreshed every second, based on request. This table is only supported on CES/CER.

brcdNPBufferErrorEntry.name: brcdNPBufferErrorEntry
brcdNPBufferErrorEntry.description: An entry containing buffer error event counter information applicable for a set of interfaces managed by a NP.

brcdNPBufferErrorSlotId.name: brcdNPBufferErrorSlotId
brcdNPBufferErrorSlotId.description: Slot ID of the module, which uniquely identifies it. The module must be physically present and operationally up. This is 1-based index.

brcdNPBufferErrorDeviceId.name: brcdNPBufferErrorDeviceId
brcdNPBufferErrorDeviceId.description: The NP device ID, a number which uniquely identifies the network processor within a module in the system. This is 1-based index.

brcdNPBufferErrorDescription.name: brcdNPBufferErrorDescription
brcdNPBufferErrorDescription.description: This object gives the range of ports serviced by the NP identified by brcdNPBufferErrorSlotId and brcdNPBufferDeviceId.

brcdNPBufferErrorIngressCurrentEvents.name: brcdNPBufferErrorIngressCurrentEvents
brcdNPBufferErrorIngressCurrentEvents.description: Counter for NP Ingress buffer error events recorded within a window.

brcdNPBufferErrorIngressCumulativeEvents.name: brcdNPBufferErrorIngressCumulativeEvents
brcdNPBufferErrorIngressCumulativeEvents.description: Counter for NP Ingress total buffer error events recorded.

brcdNPBufferErrorEgressCurrentEvents.name: brcdNPBufferErrorEgressCurrentEvents
brcdNPBufferErrorEgressCurrentEvents.description: Counter for NP Egress buffer error events recorded within a window.

brcdNPBufferErrorEgressCumulativeEvents.name: brcdNPBufferErrorEgressCumulativeEvents
brcdNPBufferErrorEgressCumulativeEvents.description: Counter for NP Egress total buffer error events recorded

brcdNPCSRAMErrorTable.name: brcdNPCSRAMErrorTable
brcdNPCSRAMErrorTable.description: A list of brcdNPCSRAMError entries. This table contains information of various Network Processor(NP) CSRAM error event counters supported by this system. The objects in this table are refreshed every second, based on request. This table is only supported on CES and CER.

brcdNPCSRAMErrorEntry.name: brcdNPCSRAMErrorEntry
brcdNPCSRAMErrorEntry.description: An entry containing CSRAM error event counter information applicable for a set of interfaces managed by a NP.

brcdNPCSRAMErrorSlotId.name: brcdNPCSRAMErrorSlotId
brcdNPCSRAMErrorSlotId.description: Slot-id of the module which uniquely identifies it in the system. The module should be physically present and should be UP. This is a 1-based index.

brcdNPCSRAMErrorDeviceId.name: brcdNPCSRAMErrorDeviceId
brcdNPCSRAMErrorDeviceId.description: The NP device-id, a number which uniquely identifies the network processor within a module in the system. This is a 1-based index.

brcdNPCSRAMErrorDescription.name: brcdNPCSRAMErrorDescription
brcdNPCSRAMErrorDescription.description: This object gives the range of ports serviced by the NP identified by brcdNPCSRAMErrorSlotId and brcdNPCSRAMErrorDeviceId.

brcdNPCSRAMErrorCurrentEvents.name: brcdNPCSRAMErrorCurrentEvents
brcdNPCSRAMErrorCurrentEvents.description: Counter for NP CSRAM errors recorded within a configured window.

brcdNPCSRAMErrorCumulativeEvents.name: brcdNPCSRAMErrorCumulativeEvents
brcdNPCSRAMErrorCumulativeEvents.description: Counter for total NP CSRAM errors recorded.

brcdNPLPMRAMErrorTable.name: brcdNPLPMRAMErrorTable
brcdNPLPMRAMErrorTable.description: A list of brcdNPLPMRAMError entries. This table contains information of various LPM RAM error event counters supported by the Network processor in this system. The objects in this table are refreshed every second, based on request. This table is only supported on CES and CER.

brcdNPLPMRAMErrorEntry.name: brcdNPLPMRAMErrorEntry
brcdNPLPMRAMErrorEntry.description: An entry containing LPMRAM error event counter information applicable for a set of interfaces managed by a NP.

brcdNPLPMRAMErrorIndex.name: brcdNPLPMRAMErrorIndex
brcdNPLPMRAMErrorIndex.description: This object uniquely identifies a LPM within a network processor. CER devices use LPM-0, LPM-1 and LPM-2 memories, whereas CES devices use LPM-3 memory only. This is a 1-based index. Therefore, index value of 1 maps to LPM0, 2 maps to LPM1 and so on.

brcdNPLPMRAMErrorSlotId.name: brcdNPLPMRAMErrorSlotId
brcdNPLPMRAMErrorSlotId.description: Slot-id of the module which uniquely identifies it in the system. The module should be physically present and should be UP. This is a 1-based index.

brcdNPLPMRAMErrorDeviceId.name: brcdNPLPMRAMErrorDeviceId
brcdNPLPMRAMErrorDeviceId.description: The NP device-id, a number which uniquely identifies the network processor within a module in the system. This is a 1-based index.

brcdNPLPMRAMErrorName.name: brcdNPLPMRAMErrorName
brcdNPLPMRAMErrorName.description: This object gives a string representing the LPM identified by brcdNPLPMRAMErrorIndex.

brcdNPLPMRAMErrorDescription.name: brcdNPLPMRAMErrorDescription
brcdNPLPMRAMErrorDescription.description: This object gives the range of ports serviced by the NP identified by brcdNPLPMRAMErrorSlotId and brcdNPLPMRAMErrorDeviceId.

brcdNPLPMRAMErrorCurrentEvents.name: brcdNPLPMRAMErrorCurrentEvents
brcdNPLPMRAMErrorCurrentEvents.description: Counter for the error events recorded within a configured window in the LPM identified by brcdNPLPMRAMErrorIndex, brcdNPLPMRAMErrorSlotId and brcdNPLPMRAMErrorDeviceId.

brcdNPLPMRAMErrorCumulativeEvents.name: brcdNPLPMRAMErrorCumulativeEvents
brcdNPLPMRAMErrorCumulativeEvents.description: Counter for the error events recorded within a configured window in the LPM identified by brcdNPLPMRAMErrorIndex, brcdNPLPMRAMErrorSlotId and brcdNPLPMRAMErrorDeviceId.

brcdNPQosStatTable.name: brcdNPQosStatTable
brcdNPQosStatTable.description: This table contains information of Qos counters for the specific interface per Qos priority. Please refer to the MIB reference guide for pre-requisites of this table.

brcdNPQosStatEntry.name: brcdNPQosStatEntry
brcdNPQosStatEntry.description: An entry containing Qos statistics information applicable for a particular interface.

brcdNPQosStatIfIndex.name: brcdNPQosStatIfIndex
brcdNPQosStatIfIndex.description: ifIndex of the interface. All the interfaces of the LP modules that are physically present and operationally up will be included in this table. Starting from NetIron 5.3 release, all deployed LAG interfaces will also be included in this table.

brcdNPQosStatQosPriority.name: brcdNPQosStatQosPriority
brcdNPQosStatQosPriority.description: Qos priority associated with this entry. This is 1-based index. The priority0 maps to 1, priority1 maps to 2 etc. Priority value equal to nonPriority(128) is not applicable to this table.

brcdNPQosStatIngressPkts.name: brcdNPQosStatIngressPkts
brcdNPQosStatIngressPkts.description: The number of packets that have arrived on the specified interface with a DSCP, EXP or PCP value equal to the value of the brcdNPQosStatQosPriority object.

brcdNPQosStatIngressBytes.name: brcdNPQosStatIngressBytes
brcdNPQosStatIngressBytes.description: The number of bytes that have arrived on the specified interface with a DSCP, EXP or PCP value in the packet equal to the value of the brcdNPQosStatQosPriority object.

brcdNPQosStatEgressPkts.name: brcdNPQosStatEgressPkts
brcdNPQosStatEgressPkts.description: The number of packets leaving the device on the specified interface with an internal priority value equal to the value of the brcdNPQosStatQosPriority object. The internal priority is configuration dependent but generally is a function of DSCP, EXP or PCP.

brcdNPQosStatEgressBytes.name: brcdNPQosStatEgressBytes
brcdNPQosStatEgressBytes.description: The number of bytes leaving the device on the specified interface with an internal priority value equal to the value of the brcdNPQosStatQosPriority object. The internal priority is configuration dependent but generally is a function of DSCP, EXP or PCP.

brcdNPDebugStatTable.name: brcdNPDebugStatTable
brcdNPDebugStatTable.description: This table contains the debug statistics of Network Processors in the line cards.

brcdNPDebugStatEntry.name: brcdNPDebugStatEntry
brcdNPDebugStatEntry.description: An entry containing debug statistics of a Network Processor

brcdNPDebugStatSlotId.name: brcdNPDebugStatSlotId
brcdNPDebugStatSlotId.description: Slot ID of the LP module, which uniquely identifies a linecard. The LP module must be physically present and operationally up.

brcdNPDebugStatNPDeviceId.name: brcdNPDebugStatNPDeviceId
brcdNPDebugStatNPDeviceId.description: The NP device ID, a number which uniquely identifies the network processor within a linecard in the system.

brcdNPDebugStatDescription.name: brcdNPDebugStatDescription
brcdNPDebugStatDescription.description: This object gives the range of ports serviced by the brcdNPDebugStatNPDeviceId.

brcdNPDebugStatL2SourceAddrLearnDrop.name: brcdNPDebugStatL2SourceAddrLearnDrop
brcdNPDebugStatL2SourceAddrLearnDrop.description: A count of all L2 source address learning drop packets.

brcdNPDebugStatRateLimitVPLSLocalLearnDr.name: brcdNPDebugStatRateLimitVPLSLocalLearnDrop
brcdNPDebugStatRateLimitVPLSLocalLearnDr.description: A count of all rate limit VPLS local learning drop packets.

brcdNPDebugStatUnkownMPLSDrop.name: brcdNPDebugStatUnkownMPLSDrop
brcdNPDebugStatUnkownMPLSDrop.description: A count of all unknow MPLS drop packets. It includes packets with Unknow Label to CPU (or) MPLS Label TTL <=1 (or) L2VPN Packet but PRAM type not equal to VLL or VPLS (or) MPLS transit label TTL <=1.

brcdNPDebugStatDestAddrVCMiss.name: brcdNPDebugStatDestAddrVCMiss
brcdNPDebugStatDestAddrVCMiss.description: A count of all destination address VC lookup miss packets.

brcdNPDebugStatRateLimitVPLSRemoteLearnD.name: brcdNPDebugStatRateLimitVPLSRemoteLearnDrop
brcdNPDebugStatRateLimitVPLSRemoteLearnD.description: A count of all rate limit VPLS remote learn drop packets.

brcdNPDebugStatIPv4DestAddrVCMiss.name: brcdNPDebugStatIPv4DestAddrVCMiss
brcdNPDebugStatIPv4DestAddrVCMiss.description: A count of all IPv4 destination address VC lookup miss packets.

brcdNPDebugStatIPv6DestAddrVCMiss.name: brcdNPDebugStatIPv6DestAddrVCMiss
brcdNPDebugStatIPv6DestAddrVCMiss.description: A count of all IPv6 destination address VC lookup miss packets.

brcdNPDebugStatVPLSTx.name: brcdNPDebugStatVPLSTx
brcdNPDebugStatVPLSTx.description: A count of all VPLS destination address hit Tx processing packets.

brcdNPDebugStatVLLTx.name: brcdNPDebugStatVLLTx
brcdNPDebugStatVLLTx.description: A count of all VLL destination address hit Tx processing packets.

brcdNPDebugStatUnknowL3VPNIngressDrop.name: brcdNPDebugStatUnknowL3VPNIngressDrop
brcdNPDebugStatUnknowL3VPNIngressDrop.description: A count of all unknown L3 VPN ingress drop packets. It includes outer IP checksum fail (or) TTL=0 (or) routing not enabled packets.

brcdNPDebugStatIPv6VPNTx.name: brcdNPDebugStatIPv6VPNTx
brcdNPDebugStatIPv6VPNTx.description: A count of all IPv6 VPN transmit processing packets.

brcdNPDebugStatIPv4VPNTx.name: brcdNPDebugStatIPv4VPNTx
brcdNPDebugStatIPv4VPNTx.description: A count of all IPv4 VPN transmit processing packets.

brcdNPDebugStatGREIPv4RxCount.name: brcdNPDebugStatGREIPv4RxCount
brcdNPDebugStatGREIPv4RxCount.description: A count of all GRE encapsulated IPv4 payload packets proceeded for IP DPA processing.

brcdNPDebugStatGREInvalidDrop.name: brcdNPDebugStatGREInvalidDrop
brcdNPDebugStatGREInvalidDrop.description: A count of all packets with invalid protocol type in GRE header.

brcdNPDebugStat6to4RxCount.name: brcdNPDebugStat6to4RxCount
brcdNPDebugStat6to4RxCount.description: A count of all valid outer IPv4 header and source ingress check hit packets.

brcdNPDebugStatGREEnfSourceIngressChkMis.name: brcdNPDebugStatGREEnfSourceIngressChkMiss
brcdNPDebugStatGREEnfSourceIngressChkMis.description: A count of all GRE outer IPv4 source ingress check miss packets.

brcdNPDebugStat6to4EnfSourceIngressChkMi.name: brcdNPDebugStat6to4EnfSourceIngressChkMiss
brcdNPDebugStat6to4EnfSourceIngressChkMi.description: A count of all outer IPv4 source ingress check miss packets.

brcdNPDebugStatGREMPLSRxCount.name: brcdNPDebugStatGREMPLSRxCount
brcdNPDebugStatGREMPLSRxCount.description: A count of all GRE encapsulated MPLS payload packets proceeded for MPLS receive processing.

brcdNPDebugStatGREIPv6RxCount.name: brcdNPDebugStatGREIPv6RxCount
brcdNPDebugStatGREIPv6RxCount.description: A count of all GRE encapsulated IPv6 payload packets proceeded for IP DPA processing.

brcdNPDebugStatPBBRxDropCount.name: brcdNPDebugStatPBBRxDropCount
brcdNPDebugStatPBBRxDropCount.description: A count of all PBB Rx drop packets.This counter is valid only for 2*100G, 8*10G, 4*40G, 'BR-MLX-10Gx20 20-port 1/10GbE Module', 'BR-MLX-100Gx2-CFP2 2-port 100GbE Module' and 'BR-MLX-10Gx4-M-IPSEC 4-port 10GbE Module' cards.

brcdNPDebugStatPBBTxCount.name: brcdNPDebugStatPBBTxCount
brcdNPDebugStatPBBTxCount.description: A count of all PBB Tx packets.This counter is valid only for 2*100G, 8*10G, 4*40G, 'BR-MLX-10Gx20 20-port 1/10GbE Module', 'BR-MLX-100Gx2-CFP2 2-port 100GbE Module' and 'BR-MLX-10Gx4-M-IPSEC 4-port 10GbE Module' cards.

brcdNPDebugStatIPv4DestAddrVCDrop.name: brcdNPDebugStatIPv4DestAddrVCDrop
